comment:
The latest is that Amber's lawyer has admitted that Amber still, 4 years later, hasn't made the charitable donations she had pledged to out of her divorce settlement, despite Amber stating in interviews and in court proceedings that she had done so.  Johnny's lawyer has made an emergency petition to the court for all documents of Amber's donations as those claims are a basis for her credibility and for her motivation for making the false DV claims.

Amber publicly stated she would give her $7M divorce settlement to 2 charities (aclu and a children's hospital).  She stated in interviews, "it's not about the money" and in the audios with Johnny, she complained people were calling her a gold digger.  She even used the donation as justification in the UK trial that Johnny's claim that her DV allegations were to get money from him.  The UK judge relied on that argument in his finding that Amber was a reliable witness and then siding with her.  So, if Amber still hasn't made any donation out of the $7m she pledged, it throws her argument that she's not a gold digger out the window and it punches a big old hole in her credibility.
